The paper focuses on attacks on automatic speech recognition and voice identification systems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of speech processing (cs.SD) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The attacks are designed to be black-box and transferable, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of signal degradation on the attacks, which could be relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
